The 76-year-old's Isuzu D-Max ute and attached white caravan were parked at a service station on the remote Great Northern Highway in Halls Creek about 10.45am yesterday.The owner was inspecting the caravan when it's alleged somebody got into the ute and drove off, hitting him.He suffered life-threatening injuries and was flown via the Royal Flying Doctor Service to the Royal Darwin Hospital.The ute and caravan, which have South Australian number plates, are still missing. items.standfirst: Amid severe shortages and pressure from Donald Trump's "reciprocal tariffs", Japan is under unprecedented pressure to eat more foreign rice. Here's why that's controversial.
items.content: Amid severe shortages and pressure from Donald Trump's "reciprocal tariffs", Japan is under unprecedented pressure to eat more foreign rice. Here's why that's controversial.

clusters.ai_summary:
• Japan faces a rice shortage, causing a crisis.
• The country is under pressure to import more foreign rice.
• Donald Trump's "reciprocal tariffs" added pressure.
• The debate involves food security and national identity.
• The article explains why this is a controversial issue.

clusters.title: Modular homes can be built quickly and cheaply. But there's an image problem
clusters.neutral_headline: Modular homes offer quick, cheap construction, but face image issues

items.title: Modular homes can be built quickly and cheaply. But there's an image problem
items.standfirst: From early colonial settlers to the post-war construction boom, prefabricated and modular housing has a long history in Australia. Can factory-built homes fix our housing woes and help the climate?
items.content: From early colonial settlers to the post-war construction boom, prefabricated and modular housing has a long history in Australia. Can factory-built homes fix our housing woes and help the climate?

clusters.ai_summary:
• Modular homes can be built quickly and affordably.
• They have a long history in Australia.
• Prefabricated and modular housing has been around for a while.
• The article asks if they can fix housing woes.
• The article also asks if they can help the climate.
